clinical_study.brief_title: A Study of CLN-619 Alone and in Combination With Pembrolizumab in Advanced Solid Tumors
clinical_study.official_title: A Phase 1 Dose-Escalation Study to Investigate the Safety, Efficacy, Pharmacokinetics, and Pharmacodynamic Activity of CLN-619 (Anti-MICA/MICB Antibody) Alone and in Combination With Pembrolizumab in Patients With Advanced Solid Tumors

brief_summary.textblock: CLN-619-001 is a Phase 1, open-label, multi-center study of CLN-619 alone and in combination with pembrolizumab in patients with advanced solid tumors.

primary_outcome.description: Number of treatment-emergent events (TEAEs) TEAE is defined as adverse events reported for the first time or worsening of a pre-existing event after the first dose of study drug.

primary_outcome.time_frame: Every 9 weeks for the first two years and then every 12 weeks until disease progression; approximately 36 months
primary_outcome.description: Best Overall Response (BOR): The % of patients having a CR or PR as determined by PI assessment of disease response per RECIST 1.1 on at least one scan.

primary_outcome.time_frame: Every 9 weeks for the first two years and then every 12 weeks until disease progression; approximately 36 months
primary_outcome.description: Overall Response Rate (ORR): The % of patients having a CR or PR as determined by PI assessment of disease response per RECIST 1.1.

primary_outcome.time_frame: Every 9 weeks for the first two years and then every 12 weeks until disease progression; approximately 36 months
primary_outcome.description: Duration of Response (DoR): The time from the earliest date of CR or PR until the earliest date of disease progression, as determined by PI assessment of disease response per RECIST 1.1 or death from any cause if occurring sooner than progression.

primary_outcome.time_frame: Every 9 weeks for the first two years and then every 12 weeks until disease progression; approximately 36 months
primary_outcome.description: Disease Control Rate (DCR): The % of participants having CR, PR, or SD as best on study response.

primary_outcome.time_frame: Every 9 weeks for the first two years and then every 12 weeks until disease progression; approximately 36 months
primary_outcome.description: Overall Survival (OS): Time from the initial date of treatment until death.

primary_outcome.time_frame: Every 9 weeks for the first two years and then every 12 weeks until disease progression; approximately 36 months
primary_outcome.description: Clinical Benefit Rate (CBR): The % of participants who achieve CR, PR or SD for a duration of 6 months as determined by PI assessment of disease response per RECIST 1.1.

secondary_outcome.description: Area under the curve up to tau (AUCtau) of CLN-619
Last validated plasma concentration (Clast) of CLN-619
